The paper focuses on the development of intelligent robots that can understand both the geometric and semantic properties of their environment. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Robotics (cs.RO) sub-category. Additionally, the paper leverages deep-learning object detection and 3D unsupervised segmentation, which are techniques commonly used in Computer Vision (cs.CV) and Machine Learning (cs.LG, cs.AI) research. Finally, the paper also involves natural language processing, which is a topic covered in the Computational Linguistics (cs.CL) sub-category.
